really active women in the political side of the

05:11.825 --> 05:16.149
university. But see. Were there any obstacles you 
all had to overcome? No, because we had, you know,

05:21.834 --> 05:31.624
the only obstacle we had, I guess, was just 
tradition, because Rutter would not consider

05:21.834 --> 05:31.624
having a faculty senate. Williams would have, but 
it was just before its time. Well, here comes our

05:34.587 --> 05:37.990
president from Rice University, who was very 
open, very faculty-oriented, and

05:38.628 --> 05:49.847
Frank was very interested in the future, 
visioning, and didn't like committee meetings

05:38.628 --> 05:49.847
too much. Now, this is true. He didn't like 
committee meetings too much, but he was a great

05:51.510 --> 05:55.256
faculty president. He really was 
faculty-oriented, and I told him that every time I

05:56.138 --> 06:00.525
saw him. And he helped us make this faculty senate 
work. So I'll always admire that man a great deal.

06:06.444 --> 06:09.728
And who was the chief academic officer at that 
time? McDonald, let's see. Donald McDonald?

06:13.413 --> 06:17.199
Yeah, Donald McDonald was one of the chief 
academics. Because Prescott had already.

